The paper proposes a deep convolutional neural network for face detection, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The network leverages facial attributes based supervision, which involves training the network to classify attributes from uncropped face images, indicating a potential focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the emergence of part detectors within the network, which could relate to multimedia (cs.MM) or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
